laboratory_examinations.findings: The gallbladder wall is thick and edematous, measuring 6 mm, with fat stranding in the surrounding tissue, concerning for cholecystitis. No focal lesions are seen in the liver. The spleen, adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal in appearance. The pancreas is atrophic. There is a biliary stent in place. No periportal, mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. The abdominal aorta is within normal limits. No free fluid. No free air. The large and small bowel appear within normal limits. Two well-circumscribed lytic lesions within the L4 vertebral body adjacent to the superior endplate with surrounding sclerosis are seen again.
